1
00:01:40,660 --> 00:01:42,000
=What If=

2
00:01:42,000 --> 00:01:44,980
=What If=

3
00:01:44,980 --> 00:01:47,860
=Episode 3=
(Within Reach And Out of Reach)

4
00:01:49,514 --> 00:01:51,380
Regarding
the live stream incident yesterday,

5
00:01:52,550 --> 00:01:54,270
I've already discussed it with Ms. Chen.

6
00:01:54,270 --> 00:01:55,980
Take disciplinary actions
against you alone.

7
00:01:55,990 --> 00:01:57,914
We'll deduct 3,000 yuan
from your monthly wage.

8
00:01:58,020 --> 00:01:58,830
Mr. Xue,

9
00:01:59,500 --> 00:02:01,190
why am I the only one punished?

10
00:02:01,190 --> 00:02:03,410
I didn't give Xiao Jie the order
to replenish the goods.

11
00:02:03,420 --> 00:02:04,270
It was Tim.

12
00:02:04,885 --> 00:02:06,780
I can accept it
if I was punished with him...

13
00:02:06,780 --> 00:02:09,660
The encrypted key for backend goods
replenishment is only accessible

14
00:02:09,660 --> 00:02:12,430
on the PCs meant for
the Marketing Department, am I right?

15
00:02:14,150 --> 00:02:16,590
Mr. Xue, firstly,

16
00:02:17,100 --> 00:02:19,150
I'm not the one mainly
responsible for the mistake.

17
00:02:19,380 --> 00:02:20,100
Secondly,

18
00:02:20,220 --> 00:02:21,500
the company has never designated

19
00:02:21,500 --> 00:02:24,100
the maximum quantity limits
for different sales channels, right?

20
00:02:24,110 --> 00:02:25,870
The more products we sell
through e-commerce,

21
00:02:25,870 --> 00:02:27,942
the more money
our company will make as well.

22
00:02:30,260 --> 00:02:32,070
Did Chen Nan tell you that?

23
00:02:34,590 --> 00:02:35,350
She just thinks

24
00:02:35,350 --> 00:02:36,780
that you should support and promote

25
00:02:36,870 --> 00:02:40,220
more cooperation
with our live-stream e-commerce.

26
00:02:40,230 --> 00:02:42,630
There's a limited amount of space
one can occupy in that field.

27
00:02:42,630 --> 00:02:43,430
If we don't occupy it,

28
00:02:43,430 --> 00:02:44,540
- the others...
- Xia Guo.

29
00:02:47,980 --> 00:02:50,070
The resource allocation

30
00:02:50,380 --> 00:02:52,030
for both online and offline channels

31
00:02:52,220 --> 00:02:54,870
cannot be decided by me or her alone,

32
00:02:56,030 --> 00:02:56,940
not to mention you.

33
00:02:59,540 --> 00:03:00,820
Understood?

34
00:03:01,310 --> 00:03:02,940
Is there anything else?

35
00:03:05,380 --> 00:03:06,500
The door is behind you.

36
00:03:16,030 --> 00:03:17,940
Let's not drag this out any longer.

37
00:03:18,190 --> 00:03:19,430
Let's hurry and deal with this.

38
00:03:19,870 --> 00:03:21,070
Ms. Nan, are you okay?

39
00:03:21,070 --> 00:03:21,780
Okay.

40
00:03:22,820 --> 00:03:23,540
Alright.

41
00:03:24,590 --> 00:03:25,260
Ms. Nan,

42
00:03:25,430 --> 00:03:26,980
why must I take the blame?

43
00:03:26,980 --> 00:03:28,260
It was obviously Tim's fault.

44
00:03:28,260 --> 00:03:30,800
Many things in life cannot be discerned
by right or wrong alone.

45
00:03:30,870 --> 00:03:32,220
Don't you know that?

46
00:03:33,571 --> 00:03:35,500
Even so, the company
has to be reasonable.

47
00:03:35,750 --> 00:03:37,680
This isn't fair
to the Marketing Department.

48
00:03:38,030 --> 00:03:39,640
How can we proceed with our work now?

49
00:03:40,150 --> 00:03:41,820
The wrongdoer wasn't punished.

50
00:03:41,820 --> 00:03:43,460
The people beside him
are punished instead.

51
00:03:43,470 --> 00:03:44,630
There's no way I can do this.

52
00:03:44,660 --> 00:03:45,940
If so, you should leave.

53
00:03:46,590 --> 00:03:47,750
No one will stop you.

54
00:03:49,150 --> 00:03:49,870
Xia Guo,

55
00:03:50,171 --> 00:03:52,400
why did you come to Shanghai
in the first place?

56
00:03:53,780 --> 00:03:54,750
I'm here to make money.

57
00:03:55,190 --> 00:03:57,100
If so, you have to be capable enough.

58
00:03:57,780 --> 00:03:59,260
Didn't you promise me in Leshan

59
00:03:59,500 --> 00:04:00,940
that you could withstand pressure?

60
00:04:01,260 --> 00:04:03,700
You can't take it when you're
dealing with such a minor issue?

61
00:04:04,260 --> 00:04:05,910
Seems like I was wrong about you.

62
00:04:07,430 --> 00:04:08,430
How about I tell

63
00:04:08,440 --> 00:04:10,620
the Finance Department
to book a flight for you this afternoon.

64
00:04:10,630 --> 00:04:11,630
You may leave anytime.

65
00:04:16,571 --> 00:04:17,670
I don't want to go back.

66
00:04:18,110 --> 00:04:19,750
If so, you should do your best here.

67
00:04:20,000 --> 00:04:22,930
The issues you'll encounter later
will be much more troublesome than it.

68
00:04:22,940 --> 00:04:25,000
You're actually dejected
over such a minor issue?

69
00:04:25,190 --> 00:04:26,900
Don't be a snowflake.

70
00:04:28,110 --> 00:04:30,110
And, I need to remind you of this.

71
00:04:30,670 --> 00:04:32,990
Xue Yuming is not just picking on
the Marketing Department,

72
00:04:32,990 --> 00:04:34,880
but he's also picking on me
most of the time.

73
00:04:34,940 --> 00:04:36,380
And, you're the person I recruited.

74
00:04:36,700 --> 00:04:39,310
You have to be extra careful
in the future. Understood?

75
00:04:41,340 --> 00:04:42,670
Got it, Ms. Nan.

76
00:04:45,670 --> 00:04:46,670
Here.

77
00:04:48,628 --> 00:04:51,430
I have plenty of meal appointments
this month. I'm not using my meal card.

78
00:04:51,440 --> 00:04:53,310
We above the mid-tier
have meal allowances.

79
00:04:53,310 --> 00:04:55,028
It'll go to waste if you don't use it.

80
00:04:55,140 --> 00:04:56,550
Just take it. My hands are sore.

81
00:05:01,700 --> 00:05:02,940
Go and have something meal.

82
00:05:03,314 --> 00:05:05,000
After that, come back and work harder.

83
00:05:26,460 --> 00:05:28,140
(Haowei Food Group)

84
00:05:28,140 --> 00:05:28,870
(That GM of yours)

85
00:05:28,870 --> 00:05:29,900
(is too much.)

86
00:05:31,670 --> 00:05:33,070
He's inhumane.

87
00:05:33,500 --> 00:05:35,380
He's worse than Wang Chang'an.

88
00:05:35,380 --> 00:05:36,670
I have to live in fear every day.

89
00:05:37,110 --> 00:05:38,110
Luckily, I have Ms. Nan.

90
00:05:38,940 --> 00:05:40,870
She gave me
her meal card this afternoon.

91
00:05:41,430 --> 00:05:43,020
I'm sure she knew my wage was docked.

92
00:05:43,085 --> 00:05:44,085
She felt sorry for me.

93
00:05:44,142 --> 00:05:46,285
Luckily, you have Ms. Chen
covering your back.

94
00:05:46,630 --> 00:05:47,900
If so, why are you eating that?

95
00:05:48,750 --> 00:05:50,460
I'm too shy to use it.

96
00:05:50,828 --> 00:05:52,800
I'm already grateful
that she's this nice to me.

97
00:05:53,020 --> 00:05:55,020
Yeah. We don't lack that money either.

98
00:05:55,285 --> 00:05:58,020
(Oh, is Mr. Yu going to be transferred
to another hospital tomorrow?)

99
00:05:58,030 --> 00:06:00,340
(If so, you don't need to be
on the night shift every day.)

100
00:06:00,714 --> 00:06:01,857
That's not happening.

101
00:06:01,914 --> 00:06:03,114
My mother is worried about him.

102
00:06:03,190 --> 00:06:05,714
(She insists on letting him
stay here for a few more days.)

103
00:06:08,900 --> 00:06:09,900
Is that so?

104
00:06:10,750 --> 00:06:12,750
That's good too. At least
his condition is stable.

105
00:06:13,380 --> 00:06:14,750
However, it'll be hard on you.

106
00:06:15,230 --> 00:06:15,940
It's not that bad.

107
00:06:16,230 --> 00:06:17,190
Actually,

108
00:06:17,190 --> 00:06:18,800
I'm not on night shift duty every day.

109
00:06:19,340 --> 00:06:21,500
By the way, stop
mailing stuff to my parents.

110
00:06:21,885 --> 00:06:23,260
(You got yourself a terrible GM.)

111
00:06:23,500 --> 00:06:24,685
(You should keep the money,)

112
00:06:24,742 --> 00:06:25,990
(buy meals for your colleagues,)

113
00:06:26,000 --> 00:06:27,980
(and try to foster
good relationships with them.)

114
00:06:30,020 --> 00:06:32,580
I don't want to foster relationships
with other people.

115
00:06:34,340 --> 00:06:36,550
Yam Head, you should come here quickly.

116
00:06:37,260 --> 00:06:39,340
I don't wish to be alone anymore.

117
00:06:40,340 --> 00:06:41,340
Don't cry.

118
00:06:42,020 --> 00:06:44,750
If you cry, it feels like
I'm bullying you.

119
00:06:47,670 --> 00:06:48,310
By the way,

120
00:06:48,342 --> 00:06:49,340
I have a gift for you.

121
00:06:49,500 --> 00:06:50,580
What is it?

122
00:06:52,340 --> 00:06:53,430
An oscillator?

123
00:06:53,900 --> 00:06:55,260
Why did you buy that?

124
00:06:55,400 --> 00:06:57,460
Who told you to make yourself
look so pitiful?

125
00:06:57,542 --> 00:06:59,600
You couldn't bear
to clean your ears outside.

126
00:06:59,670 --> 00:07:01,460
I was just exaggerating it.

127
00:07:01,790 --> 00:07:03,940
I was just unhappy with
the cost of living here.

128
00:07:04,190 --> 00:07:05,020
Now, you know.

129
00:07:05,380 --> 00:07:07,310
Your boyfriend's service
is still valuable.

130
00:07:07,457 --> 00:07:08,820
You can't live without me, right?

131
00:07:08,820 --> 00:07:09,700
Here, listen to this.

132
00:07:15,140 --> 00:07:17,070
I miss you so much!

133
00:07:17,630 --> 00:07:20,000
Why are you crying again?

134
00:07:20,310 --> 00:07:22,670
Should I cry too and join in the fun?

135
00:07:29,190 --> 00:07:29,990
What's wrong?

136
00:07:30,790 --> 00:07:31,640
I'll hang up first.

137
00:07:31,685 --> 00:07:32,630
Something cropped up.

138
00:07:32,630 --> 00:07:33,940
Hello?

139
00:07:41,314 --> 00:07:42,550
You're still working overtime?

140
00:07:49,230 --> 00:07:50,940
Why are you having
our competitor's product

141
00:07:51,285 --> 00:07:53,200
instead of
the company's self-heating hot pot?

142
00:07:54,840 --> 00:07:56,310
This is Bowl Chicken-Flavored.

143
00:07:56,380 --> 00:07:57,971
Our company doesn't have this flavor.

144
00:07:58,550 --> 00:08:00,900
And, I just want to know

145
00:08:00,900 --> 00:08:03,430
the strengths and weaknesses
of our competitor's products.

146
00:08:05,657 --> 00:08:07,028
You're from Sichuan, huh?

147
00:08:07,500 --> 00:08:08,380
Bowl Chicken.

148
00:08:08,828 --> 00:08:10,457
Are you only having this for dinner?

149
00:08:13,630 --> 00:08:14,820
My wage was just docked.

150
00:08:14,914 --> 00:08:16,260
What else can I eat besides this?

151
00:08:16,270 --> 00:08:18,490
Mr. Xue, could it be
that you wish to treat me to a meal?

152
00:08:18,500 --> 00:08:19,700
Sure, I'll treat you to a meal.

153
00:08:20,260 --> 00:08:21,430
What do you want?

154
00:08:24,870 --> 00:08:25,790
Forget it.

155
00:08:26,430 --> 00:08:27,670
I haven't finished my work yet.

156
00:08:27,714 --> 00:08:29,571
I don't want my wage to be docked again.

157
00:08:34,190 --> 00:08:34,820
Okay.

158
00:08:42,150 --> 00:08:43,980
Didn't you realize

159
00:08:44,142 --> 00:08:46,100
that I was being concerned
about you just now?

160
00:08:53,150 --> 00:08:54,670
Alright. Don't stay here too late.

161
00:08:54,940 --> 00:08:56,030
Go back early.

162
00:09:11,670 --> 00:09:13,030
Why are you only here now?

163
00:09:13,620 --> 00:09:14,510
Where did you go?

164
00:09:14,520 --> 00:09:15,990
I went to set up our display in IKEA.

165
00:09:16,000 --> 00:09:17,940
I saw the text in our group chat
and I rushed here.

166
00:09:17,940 --> 00:09:18,580
What's going on?

167
00:09:18,580 --> 00:09:20,300
You got yourself
in huge trouble this time.

168
00:09:20,310 --> 00:09:21,460
You better don't make a sound

169
00:09:21,460 --> 00:09:22,310
when Mr. Xue is here.

170
00:09:22,310 --> 00:09:23,940
If not, he might go after you.

171
00:09:24,390 --> 00:09:25,220
Me?

172
00:09:25,980 --> 00:09:26,940
What have I done again?

173
00:09:27,510 --> 00:09:28,390
Stop. He's here.

174
00:09:44,390 --> 00:09:46,340
(Food Promotion Seminar)
Tomorrow's the first day

175
00:09:46,340 --> 00:09:48,190
of our Chinese New Year
promotional season.

176
00:09:48,390 --> 00:09:50,620
According to the feedback
from our partner,

177
00:09:51,100 --> 00:09:52,820
for the keto cake we introduced,
we still

178
00:09:52,820 --> 00:09:54,550
haven't met
the contractual requirement

179
00:09:54,550 --> 00:09:56,820
for five shopping malls' worth
of stock volume.

180
00:09:56,820 --> 00:09:58,750
They're urging us to provide them
with the goods.

181
00:09:59,790 --> 00:10:02,550
But our warehouse in Shanghai
has run out of goods.

182
00:10:03,740 --> 00:10:05,100
Now, it's 4 PM.

183
00:10:05,390 --> 00:10:07,670
We have 18 hours until 10 AM tomorrow,

184
00:10:07,820 --> 00:10:10,000
which is the operating hour
for shopping malls.

185
00:10:12,314 --> 00:10:13,740
Guys, how should we resolve this?

186
00:10:15,700 --> 00:10:18,940
Why don't I speak to Xiao Jie first?

187
00:10:18,971 --> 00:10:20,820
I'll tell her to delay
the online shipments

188
00:10:20,885 --> 00:10:23,580
and transfer half of the inventory here
to support our offline sales.

189
00:10:23,742 --> 00:10:24,510
That's impossible.

190
00:10:24,940 --> 00:10:25,580
But why?

191
00:10:25,580 --> 00:10:27,100
Because you told me personally

192
00:10:27,110 --> 00:10:29,340
that Xiao Jie's live stream
was the first time our brand

193
00:10:29,340 --> 00:10:30,657
is making an appearance online.

194
00:10:30,670 --> 00:10:32,910
We've given the customers our promise.

195
00:10:32,940 --> 00:10:35,485
Do you want the effort
of our online customers to go in vain?

196
00:10:40,390 --> 00:10:41,820
Are you a member?

197
00:10:41,820 --> 00:10:43,670
(Free SPA)
We're doing a promotion today.

198
00:10:43,670 --> 00:10:45,620
You can enjoy our services for free.

199
00:10:47,085 --> 00:10:48,270
What about presale vouchers?

200
00:10:51,460 --> 00:10:52,430
Continue.

201
00:10:52,430 --> 00:10:53,620
Is it possible for us

202
00:10:54,070 --> 00:10:55,430
to turn the lack of goods

203
00:10:55,430 --> 00:10:57,150
into presale vouchers?

204
00:10:57,510 --> 00:10:58,900
Just like those massage parlors.

205
00:10:58,910 --> 00:11:00,270
Reload the card and get a discount.

206
00:11:00,270 --> 00:11:01,690
Then, go for the services.

207
00:11:01,700 --> 00:11:03,580
We can let our customers

208
00:11:03,580 --> 00:11:04,430
buy presale vouchers

209
00:11:04,430 --> 00:11:06,570
so that they can redeem
their products in the future.

210
00:11:06,700 --> 00:11:07,460
Lucky bag.

211
00:11:07,542 --> 00:11:08,820
We can turn it into a lucky bag.

212
00:11:08,830 --> 00:11:10,020
We'll put some free gifts inside.

213
00:11:10,030 --> 00:11:11,700
Not only
can we satisfy our customers,

214
00:11:11,980 --> 00:11:14,510
we'll also make them feel
as if they're getting a discount.

215
00:11:14,510 --> 00:11:17,740
And, we can buy time
for our production line and logistics.

216
00:11:17,980 --> 00:11:18,980
That won't do.

217
00:11:19,790 --> 00:11:21,740
Presale vouchers are viable

218
00:11:21,740 --> 00:11:23,700
for products like daily necessities.

219
00:11:23,714 --> 00:11:24,910
(Ketogenic Cake)
Our product

220
00:11:24,910 --> 00:11:26,270
isn't considered a daily necessity.

221
00:11:26,670 --> 00:11:27,980
If we use such a method,

222
00:11:28,000 --> 00:11:29,390
our customers will definitely think

223
00:11:29,430 --> 00:11:30,740
that it's a sales gimmick.

224
00:11:31,270 --> 00:11:32,460
It'll definitely affect

225
00:11:32,460 --> 00:11:33,550
their purchase experience

226
00:11:33,550 --> 00:11:35,114
and their acknowledgment of our brand.

227
00:11:35,340 --> 00:11:36,150
Moreover,

228
00:11:36,310 --> 00:11:38,740
I don't think shopping malls
will support our method.

229
00:11:41,820 --> 00:11:43,550
I do think we can give it a try.

230
00:11:48,030 --> 00:11:50,270
We can put different products
into a gift box.

231
00:11:51,580 --> 00:11:54,670
After that, we can turn it
into a lucky bag, right?

232
00:11:54,742 --> 00:11:55,620
That's right, Mr. Xue.

233
00:11:55,720 --> 00:11:57,070
Then we'll put the presale voucher

234
00:11:57,070 --> 00:11:58,885
and the samples of the five new products

235
00:11:58,885 --> 00:12:01,110
and launch in the next quarter
into the lucky bag.

236
00:12:01,620 --> 00:12:02,510
That's pretty good.

237
00:12:02,700 --> 00:12:04,460
The lucky bag can attract customers

238
00:12:04,571 --> 00:12:06,460
while we can promote
our new products too.

239
00:12:07,150 --> 00:12:08,580
I think it's a great idea.

240
00:12:12,310 --> 00:12:13,190
Ms. Chen,

241
00:12:13,800 --> 00:12:16,390
head to the Finance Department
and request a temporary budget.

242
00:12:16,400 --> 00:12:18,500
Transfer it to our suppliers'
bank accounts immediately.

243
00:12:18,510 --> 00:12:20,740
Xia Guo, go and calculate

244
00:12:20,740 --> 00:12:22,700
the number of new product samples
we need.

245
00:12:22,790 --> 00:12:23,820
If we don't have enough,

246
00:12:23,820 --> 00:12:25,930
you can fill them with
the ready goods in the warehouse.

247
00:12:25,940 --> 00:12:28,670
Lucy, find a supplier
to design our lucky bag

248
00:12:28,771 --> 00:12:29,860
and the presale vouchers.

249
00:12:29,860 --> 00:12:32,060
Then head to the warehouse
and proceed with the packaging.

250
00:12:32,070 --> 00:12:32,910
(Full of Prosperity)
Then,

251
00:12:32,910 --> 00:12:35,657
send them to the shopping malls
immediately and set up the display.

252
00:12:37,070 --> 00:12:38,030
The rest of you will be

253
00:12:38,257 --> 00:12:40,620
assigned to the warehouse
and shopping malls accordingly

254
00:12:40,620 --> 00:12:42,620
to assist in the packaging
and display set-up.

255
00:12:42,620 --> 00:12:44,940
All of you have to make sure
the lucky bags are available

256
00:12:45,000 --> 00:12:46,800
on the first day
of our promotional season.

257
00:13:05,028 --> 00:13:06,660
- Good job.
- Mr. Xue, why are you here?

258
00:13:06,670 --> 00:13:07,600
- Supper.
- Thank you.

259
00:13:07,820 --> 00:13:08,510
For everyone.

260
00:13:10,000 --> 00:13:10,860
Thank you, Mr. Xue.

261
00:13:10,860 --> 00:13:11,970
- Thanks, Mr. Xue.
- Thanks.

262
00:13:11,980 --> 00:13:12,820
Take a break.

263
00:13:21,800 --> 00:13:22,840
You should have something.

264
00:13:23,030 --> 00:13:23,910
Take a break.

265
00:13:25,114 --> 00:13:26,030
No thanks, Mr. Xue.

266
00:13:26,310 --> 00:13:27,460
I should remain in my post.

267
00:13:27,470 --> 00:13:30,285
Or I won't be able to explain myself
if something happens again.

268
00:13:31,510 --> 00:13:32,270
I'm here.

269
00:13:32,314 --> 00:13:34,857
I'll bear all of the responsibilities
if something does happen.

270
00:13:37,220 --> 00:13:38,430
Am I terrifying?

271
00:13:41,740 --> 00:13:42,740
I'm terrified of you.

272
00:13:43,428 --> 00:13:45,714
I'm terrified at the thought
that my wage might vanish.

273
00:13:53,150 --> 00:13:54,030
Sit down.

274
00:13:56,910 --> 00:13:57,980
I'll have a chat with you.

275
00:13:59,980 --> 00:14:00,980
Sit down and chat.

276
00:14:08,100 --> 00:14:09,510
You do like to bear a grudge, huh?

277
00:14:12,910 --> 00:14:14,620
You felt like you were wronged, huh?

278
00:14:16,620 --> 00:14:17,670
Fine. Let me tell you this.

279
00:14:18,100 --> 00:14:20,150
Your PC is your weapon.

280
00:14:20,771 --> 00:14:22,870
You didn't look after your weapon
and let someone

281
00:14:22,914 --> 00:14:24,200
use it without permission.

282
00:14:24,340 --> 00:14:26,670
Would you remember your lesson
if I didn't punish you?

283
00:14:31,510 --> 00:14:32,220
So, you knew

284
00:14:32,310 --> 00:14:33,430
that I was implicated by Tim?

285
00:14:33,510 --> 00:14:34,150
You don't say?

286
00:14:34,390 --> 00:14:35,620
You should've told me earlier.

287
00:14:35,828 --> 00:14:37,800
I was depressed for so long, you know?

288
00:14:39,430 --> 00:14:41,220
Now, I feel much better.

289
00:14:42,820 --> 00:14:44,220
You're happy now?

290
00:14:45,220 --> 00:14:45,940
Yeah.

291
00:14:47,914 --> 00:14:48,910
You should have some.

292
00:14:49,190 --> 00:14:49,980
Thanks.

293
00:14:50,940 --> 00:14:51,790
Good job.

294
00:14:55,685 --> 00:14:57,200
Diced Chicken With Chili Peppers?

295
00:14:57,600 --> 00:14:59,200
How did you know that I craved this?

296
00:15:00,100 --> 00:15:01,100
You're from Sichuan.

297
00:15:02,200 --> 00:15:04,685
My goodness. I have been craving
spicy food for a long time.

298
00:15:06,257 --> 00:15:07,660
Mr. Xue, don't you want some?

299
00:15:07,670 --> 00:15:08,430
I'm not hungry.

300
00:15:09,460 --> 00:15:10,100
I'll eat, then.

301
00:15:10,310 --> 00:15:11,310
Eat up.

302
00:15:14,171 --> 00:15:15,820
It tastes just like my hometown cooking.

303
00:15:24,310 --> 00:15:26,820
Mr. Xue, I have one more question.

304
00:15:27,190 --> 00:15:27,980
Ask away.

305
00:15:28,828 --> 00:15:30,790
Why did you only punish me
without punishing Tim?

306
00:15:31,340 --> 00:15:33,190
You should ask Ms. Chen about that.

307
00:15:41,940 --> 00:15:43,980
(Yam Head)

308
00:15:47,310 --> 00:15:47,860
Guo.

309
00:15:48,057 --> 00:15:49,228
What were you busy with?

310
00:15:49,310 --> 00:15:50,220
What took you so long?

311
00:15:50,314 --> 00:15:51,970
I was working overtime
in the supermarket.

312
00:15:51,980 --> 00:15:53,070
I didn't hear your call.

313
00:15:54,430 --> 00:15:55,790
My mother had a sudden headache.

314
00:15:55,885 --> 00:15:57,314
What's wrong with Mrs. Yu?

315
00:15:57,670 --> 00:15:58,430
She's fine.

316
00:15:58,542 --> 00:16:00,742
I brought her to the ER Department
to get an X-ray scan.

317
00:16:01,030 --> 00:16:03,220
However, I'm not confident
in the doctors here.

318
00:16:03,714 --> 00:16:04,860
I just want to ask you

319
00:16:05,371 --> 00:16:07,460
if you can head
to a first-tier hospital in Shanghai

320
00:16:07,470 --> 00:16:08,810
and make an appointment with them

321
00:16:08,820 --> 00:16:11,057
so that they can take
an X-ray scan for my mother?

322
00:16:11,457 --> 00:16:12,790
Which department should I go to?

323
00:16:13,628 --> 00:16:14,700
The Neurology Department.

324
00:16:15,085 --> 00:16:16,100
I'm new to the place.

325
00:16:16,220 --> 00:16:18,000
I don't know
which hospital is good enough.

326
00:16:18,780 --> 00:16:19,440
Coming!

327
00:16:19,440 --> 00:16:20,310
Guo,

328
00:16:20,320 --> 00:16:21,610
why don't you inquire about it?

329
00:16:21,620 --> 00:16:23,500
I'll hang up first.
I need to send my mom home.

330
00:16:23,510 --> 00:16:25,220
Alright, be careful, then.

331
00:16:25,220 --> 00:16:26,110
I'll talk to you later.

332
00:16:26,120 --> 00:16:26,860
Okay.

333
00:16:27,200 --> 00:16:27,820
Goodbye.

334
00:16:31,542 --> 00:16:34,100
It's hard to make an appointment
with the hospitals in Shanghai.

335
00:16:34,110 --> 00:16:35,742
Which department are you looking for?

336
00:16:36,580 --> 00:16:37,620
The Neurology Department.

337
00:16:38,310 --> 00:16:40,220
My boyfriend's mother
went for a brain CT scan.

338
00:16:40,220 --> 00:16:42,550
He wants her to come here for a checkup.

339
00:16:42,714 --> 00:16:44,430
But I don't know
which hospital to go to.

340
00:16:44,670 --> 00:16:45,430
Hospital Ruihua.

341
00:16:45,430 --> 00:16:47,730
The Neurology Department
of Hospital Ruihua is pretty good.

342
00:16:47,740 --> 00:16:49,510
You have to get a number online first.

343
00:16:49,860 --> 00:16:51,980
If you fail, you have to
line up in the hospital.

344
00:16:52,910 --> 00:16:53,670
Thank you, Mr. Xue.

345
00:16:55,220 --> 00:16:55,740
Eat up.

346
00:16:56,457 --> 00:16:57,460
Finish it while it's hot.

347
00:16:57,460 --> 00:16:58,430
Okay. Thank you.

348
00:16:59,940 --> 00:17:01,190
Hospital Ruihua.

349
00:17:10,460 --> 00:17:13,420
(Hospital Ruihua, Shanghai)

350
00:17:17,750 --> 00:17:18,270
Go now.

351
00:17:18,580 --> 00:17:19,380
Give me your paper.

352
00:17:23,990 --> 00:17:24,580
Done.

353
00:17:25,660 --> 00:17:26,510
Next.

354
00:17:27,980 --> 00:17:30,380
(Counter)

355
00:17:30,380 --> 00:17:31,070
Okay.

356
00:17:36,820 --> 00:17:37,790
Okay. Next.

